questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a `PaymentService` is failing to roll back database changes even though an exception is thrown during a sub-process. The code structure is as follows:

java
@Service
public class PaymentService {
    @Autowired
    private AccountRepository accountRepo;

    @Transactional
    public void processPayment(Long id) {
        accountRepo.updateBalance(id, -100);
        try {
            this.applyTax(id);
        } catch (RuntimeException e) {
            // Log error
        }
    }

    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void applyTax(Long id) {
        throw new RuntimeException("Tax calculation failed");
    }
}
